The paper deals with auction mechanisms and allocation games, which are topics commonly studied in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of VCG mechanisms and social welfare maximization also suggests a connection to algorithmic game theory (cs.ALG). The study of truthful and envy-free mechanisms is a central topic in mechanism design (cs.EC), and the use of payments and transfers is related to the field of computational economics (cs.CE). Finally, the focus on agent capacities and the limitations on the number of items they can receive suggests a connection to the field of combinatorial optimization (cs.DS).
